                      "ep_id": 4779,
                      "icon_url": "https://act-webstatic.hoyoverse.com/event-static-hoyowiki-admin/2023/12/20/513d51e0ebfd54f5da34a9f85dfaf61f_6342016945205081701.png",
                      "menu_id": 10,
                      "name": "Remus",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    },
                    {
                      "amount": 0,
                      "display_style": "card",
                      "ep_id": 5618,
                      "icon_url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/05/04/237301566/8387f718bf24a2a128af2225335160c5_3631573680954842438.png",
                      "menu_id": 10,
                      "name": "Boethius",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    },
                    {
                      "amount": 0,
                      "display_style": "card",
                      "ep_id": 5578,
                      "icon_url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/04/22/35428890/7557f4558ab243d82e8b6b9994fc97ee_3952883455179155002.png",
                      "menu_id": 5,
                      "name": "Fragment of Harmonic Whimsy",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    },
                    {
                      "amount": 0,
                      "display_style": "card",
                      "ep_id": 3987,
                      "icon_url": "https://upload-static.hoyoverse.com/hoyolab-wiki/2023/08/14/35428890/2cec558b676eefaafe23b64d42f2067e_6453748403910603164.png",
                      "menu_id": 4,
                      "name": "Song of Stillness",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    },
                    {
                      "amount": 0,
                      "display_style": "card",
                      "ep_id": 4325,
                      "icon_url": "https://upload-static.hoyoverse.com/hoyolab-wiki/2023/09/18/94376896/d0e75f9b88a286749b4c7dff0871e129_3058308201433029321.png",
                      "menu_id": 12,
                      "name": "The History of the Decline and Fall of Remuria",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold",
                        "color:rgb(255, 255, 255)"
                      ],
                      "text": "Canticles of Harmony",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "level": 1,
                  "type": "heading"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "alignment": "left",
                      "type": "custom_image",
                      "url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/06/21/237301566/e6ded426211e34a86d94bbb81d526d43_3962900881681456667.png"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "It was not until Boethius enacted a plan to bring back Remuria that Scylla was able to be freed from his confinement. Boethius had gained mastery over the Symphony and filled the bodies of the people of Petrichor with the souls of the long-dead Remurians. In order to save the people of Petrichor, another Harmost, Cassiodor, turned to the Traveler and Paimon for help. Together, they entered the Sea of Bygone Eras and broke the chains that bound Scylla, freeing him. Cassiodor was not at the capital when Scylla first arrived all those years ago. Due to this, he believed that Vishap-prince had betrayed the God King and attacked the Golden Palace, causing Remuria to be flooded. The Prince of Vishaps revealed the arrangement between him and Remus, their secret plan, and the creation of the Requiem, which was an order for the Grand Symphony to self-destruct. Destroying the Symphony was how the God King planned to free his subjects from their stone bodies and give them back forms of flesh and blood, destroying the artificial barrier between races. Remus was to sacrifice himself to unleash the Symphony's power, and it would fall to Scylla to control the primordial, savage energies that he would awaken. Scylla had led an army of Vishaps to assault the capital as part of Remus's final plan to save the Remurians and the nation by destroying the Grand Symphony.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "alignment": "right",
                      "type": "custom_image",
                      "url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/06/18/178140791/fa8329bb7cc10e0fd51ddf52f0c31797_9166634953437788585.png"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "Although Scylla wanted to help defeat Boethius, he was concerned that this could give the Harmost the opportunity to seize the Final Symphony that had been entrusted to him. The Dragon Prince also felt he could not help in the fight against Boethius, as he was merely a temporary occupant of an Ichor-made body. The chief strength of Dragonborn lay in their powerful flesh, embedded in Ichor as he is, all that remains of him is the feeblest of wills. Although he had lost his bodily form, he could still command the currents. Scylla roamed the ocean depths and used the currents to help aid the Traveler in the Sea of Bygone Eras.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "alignment": "left",
                      "type": "custom_image",
                      "url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/06/18/178140791/319addbf237238c198272be1f2462516_1965079358433505.png"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "With Scylla's help, the Traveler and Paimon reconnected the golden aqueducts, through which the Grand Symphony once flowed, and opened the way to the Golden Palace. The Dragon Prince bestowed the Requiem unto the Traveler, and once played, the Grand Symphony was completely destroyed, and the souls of the Remurians returned to the deep waters, to the eternal cycle of life and death. After finally fulfilling Remus's wish, Scylla brought Traveler and Paimon back to the surface. He shared his plans to seek an audience with the true Hydro Dragon, Neuvillette, as a Dragon Sovereign could not be reborn while Egeria was imprisoned in the Primordial Sea.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold",
                        "color:rgb(255, 215, 128)"
                      ],
                      "text": "Related Entries:",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
